@node intro "catool - Introduction"
catool is a programme to manage the creation and maintenance of localized
programmes and catalog-files.
If you ever wrote your own localized programme you will find it quite useful.
It is something like a GUI-front-end for CatComp.
As you may have noticed: it is thaught for programmers and translators only :-)

This is the a beta release, so there is room for developing.
@endnode


@node required "catool - System requirements"
You need at least Kickstart V39 or higher to be able to run catool.
This is necessary for lots of reasons.
OS2.04 will not and cannot be supported.

Furthermore you need "CatComp" which is available as public domain.
@endnode


@node install "catool - Installation"
To install catool you only have to copy the main programme to your
hard disk. And, since catool is localized, it may be clever to copy
the catalog-file in your Locale-directory.
Perhaps it is useful to copy this documentation along with it.

An Installer-Script is not provided yet. This may change in future
releases of the package.
@endnode


@node config "catool - Configuration"
The only configurable items are changed via tool-types. These are:

  @{b}CATCOMP=<file>@{ub}
  You can give an alternate file&path for CatComp. Default is "CatComp".

  @{b}CATCOMPOUT=<file>@{ub}
  The output of CatComp is stored here. Default is "RAM:CatComp.out".

  @{b}CATALOGS=<dir>@{ub}
  The place of your catalogs-dir. Default is "LOCALE:Catalogs".

  @{b}REPLACETEXT=<string>@{ub}
  The string contains the standard (or selected) replace-text for
  "Scan Source". Default is "GetString(&li,%s)". See "" for more details.

  @{b}TRANS=<string>@{ub}
  On programme start there is only one language to translate your
  catalogs in. Default is "deutsch".
@endnode


