@node menu "catool - The Menu"
@{u}@{b}Project                                                 @{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}New@{ub}
  Deletes the old project and creates a new one. Asks if the
  current project is not saved.

  @{b}Load...@{ub}
  Loads a #?.cd-file and the related #?.ct-files from disk.

  @{b}Save@{ub}
  Saves the current project in the current directory.

  @{b}Save as...@{ub}
  Opens a file-requester for saving.

  @{b}Update Ext.@{ub}
  Performs the CatComp-call to create the catalogs and
  source files.

  @{b}About...@{ub}
  Opens the info-requester.

  @{b}Quit@{ub}
  Quits the programme.


@{u}@{b}Options                                                 @{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}next Language@{ub}
  If selected the language turns after a given translation
  instead of going to the next message ID.

  @{b}show Min/Max@{ub}
  If selected the catalog lister shows the min/max string
  length values.

  @{b}Parameter...@{ub}
  Opens the @{"Parameter" link param}-window.

  @{b}Scan Source...@{ub}
  Opens the @{"Scan Source" link scan}-window.
@endnode


@node mainwin "catool - Main Window"
In this window you perform the actual creation and maintenanec of
your catalog-files.

With the cycle gadget in the first line you can choose the translated
language which is displayed in the list.
The buttons in the right of this gadget are used to add or remove a
language from the list. If you add a language, a window is opened where
you can enter the name of the language to be added. If you remove one
you always remove the current one which is impossible if you have
only one language in the list.

The list below these line displays the "messages" of your catalog
description and translations. With the other gadgets you can control
these messages.
Please note that you don't need to enter a number in the corresponding
field; catool counts for you - if you enter one, all the following
message numbers are changed. Enter a zero if you want to delete the
number.

With the cursor keys you are able to move in the list and change the
displayed language.
@endnode


@node param "catool - Parameter Window"
In this window you set up some parameters for your catalog-files.

In the upper group is only one string gadget where you enter the
version to be used in the "$VER"-line of your catalogs; the current
date is added there automatically.

In the first string gadget of the second group-box you define the
parameters of the CatComp-Command for the creation of source-files
and includes (see CatComp.doc for details).
This gadget accepts 2 commands:
 %f - inserts the base name of your project.
 %d - inserts the destination directory for your sources given in
      the second string gadget.
In the "Catalogs"-field you enter the directory where the #?.catalog-
files will be placed.

With the "New"- and the "Delete"-button you are able to define catalog
description commands such as #function. They are displayed in the list.
For more details on these commands, see CatComp.doc.
@endnode


